<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-25T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 (D) Regulations/9881:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Boal</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                            Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-25T15:00:00-04:00">February 25, 1943—3
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>394. Referring to Henry’s telephone conversation of February 17 with
                                    Ravndal<note n="34" xml:id="d129fn34">Christian M. Ravndal,
                                    Chief of the Division of Exports and Requirements of the
                                    Department.</note> arrangements completed for establishment of
                                decentralized export control in Bolivia effective April 1. Henry and
                                    Wilkinson<note n="35" xml:id="d129fn35">Horton Henry of the
                                    Department and H. A. Wilkinson of the Board of Economic Warfare
                                    were assigned to present a modified plan of decentralized export
                                    control in certain of the American Republics.</note> leaving for
                                Santiago on the first available airplane.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Boal</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>